</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Every bottle contains an RFID-chip which contain information like it’s color and batch number. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This information is passed to the Ink Bottle Interface (IBI) which blocks the handle if the wrong bottle is presented to the IBI. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However if the IBI is broken this blockade can be overruled and the wrong ink can be loaded. This can result in a wrong color inside the ink tank. 
